# dev/ntgcalls branch package list (see debian/rules for the full story).
# Compared to the old tgcalls/tg_owt-based build, this list shrank a lot:
# ntgcalls' own CMake fetches prebuilt/vendored copies of X11, mesa, glib,
# ffmpeg, abseil, openh264 etc itself (confirmed live via its configure
# output - "-- glib v2.89.0", "-- libX11 v1.8.13", ... - these are its own
# downloads, not pkg-config lookups against system packages), and the whole
# tg_owt/old-tgcalls CMake block (the only thing that used to consume
# libvpx-dev/libabsl-dev as real system packages) is gone. Removed:
# libabsl-dev, libvpx-dev (confirmed zero references left anywhere in this
# project's own CMakeLists.txt); libjpeg-dev, libasound2-dev, libpulse-dev,
# the libx*-dev/libxcomposite-dev cluster, libpipewire-0.3-dev, libevent-dev
# (confirmed zero references in this project's own CMakeLists.txt, PJSIP is
# built with --disable-sound so never needed alsa/pulse either - but this
# specific pruned list has NOT been re-verified with an actual from-scratch
# .deb build, only reasoned from source; if CI ever fails here on a missing
# header, that's why). libspdlog-dev/libfmt-dev also removed - spdlog is
# now built from source under the same Clang+libc++ toolchain as PJSIP/
# TDLib below (Debian's own libspdlog1.15 is GCC+libstdc++-built, mixing it
# in would reintroduce the exact ABI-collision bug class documented in
# buildenv/rename-webrtc-openssl-symbols.sh/rename-webrtc-libsrtp-symbols.sh
# one library over). libopus-dev/libavcodec-dev/etc KEPT - unlike the ones
# above, tg2sip-webrtc's own CMakeLists.txt genuinely pkg_check_modules()s
# real system opus/ffmpeg (separately from whatever copy ntgcalls itself
# also fetches for its own internal use), confirmed live via configure
# output ("Checking for module 'opus'" / "-- Found opus, version 1.3.1").
# clang-<N>/libc++-<N>-dev/libc++abi-<N>-dev deliberately NOT listed here:
# Debian's own apt doesn't carry them (bookworm's apt clang is 14, too old
# to even compile ntgcalls' vendored libc++ headers - real, confirmed
# compile errors, not just a warning), they only exist via apt.llvm.org,
# which has to be added as an apt source *before* `apt-get build-dep` can
# resolve anything from it - see the "Install newer Clang" step in
# .github/workflows/deb-packages.yml, which installs them explicitly ahead
# of the build-dep step below rather than through this file.
#
# gperf/yasm/nasm kept even though nothing in this project's own
# CMakeLists.txt/pkg-config lookups references them directly (unlike the
# ones actually removed above) - PJSIP still builds several of its own
# bundled third-party codecs (libsrtp, speex, resample, ...) from source in
# debian/rules, and unlike the X11/audio/libvpx/libabsl cluster above,
# whether any of those still need gperf/yasm/nasm for assembly-optimized
# paths wasn't specifically checked. Cheap to keep, unlike the packages
# actually pulled above; only remove after actually confirming PJSIP's own
# build doesn't reach for them.
