Package: tg2sip-webrtc
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, adduser
Description: Telegram <-> SIP voice gateway using ntgcalls (WebRTC)
 tg2sip-webrtc bridges Telegram calls (via TDLib + ntgcalls/WebRTC) to a SIP
 PBX (via PJSIP) in both directions: incoming Telegram calls can be
 forwarded to a SIP extension, and SIP can place outgoing calls to
 Telegram contacts.
 .
 This is a fork of the archived Infactum/tg2sip, replacing the defunct
 libtgvoip P2P calling protocol with pytgcalls/ntgcalls (a from-scratch,
 actively maintained WebRTC calling implementation, replacing an earlier
 tgcalls-based rewrite that could no longer negotiate the current Telegram
 calling protocol) and bumping TDLib to a version current Telegram servers
 still accept.
 .
 This package installs the tg2sip-webrtc gateway daemon (with a systemd
 service) and the tg2sip-gendb helper, used once to interactively create
 the TDLib login session (phone number, SMS code, 2FA password) before
 the daemon can run unattended.
 .
 PJSIP and TDLib are not packaged in Debian and are built from source at
 package build time; both link statically, so this package pulls in no
 runtime dependency on them.
